headline: Jamie Dimon Sees Risks in the Stock Market. It Isn’t the First Time.
summary: Former British Prime Minister Winston Churchill was quoted more than a century ago as saying that his greatest political challenge was that of “events,” or the unknown circumstances that can ultimately bring down a government.  JPMorgan Chase  boss Jamie Dimon, the son of a stockbroker and as steeped in financial market knowledge as any executive on Wall Street, has seen more than a few of his forecasts fall flat recently.  The culprit has generally been what the late Donald Rumsfeld famously described as “unknown unknowns”.
